output:
Available commands:
- create-failover-route - Create a new failover route with given policy
- delete-failover-route - Delete an existing failover route
- hello - Return the interactive welcome banner
- help - Show available commands or details for a single command
- list-failover-routes - List all configured failover routes
- loop-detection - Enable or disable loop detection for the current session
- model - Change the active model for LLM requests
- oneoff - Sets a one-time override for the backend and model for the next request.
- project - Change the active project for LLM requests
- pwd - Display the current project directory
- route-append - Append an element to a failover route
- route-clear - Clear all elements from a failover route
- route-list - List elements in a failover route
- route-prepend - Prepend an element to a failover route
- set - Set various parameters for the session
- temperature - Change the temperature setting for LLM requests
- tool-loop-detection - Enable or disable tool loop detection for the current session
- tool-loop-max-repeats - Set the maximum number of repeats for tool loop detection
- tool-loop-mode - Set the mode for tool loop detection
- tool-loop-ttl - Set the TTL (time to live) for tool loop detection in seconds
- unset - Unset (clear) various parameters for the session
